                  <persName role="owner" corresp="PRS0000">The names of the donors are mentioned in the supplication formulas throughout the Ms.: Wäldä Tǝnśaʾe (e.g., fols. 3ra, 6vb, 9vb, 10ra, 11ra, 12rb, 19ra), his wife Lahǝyä Dǝngǝl (e.g., fols. 6vb, 9vb, 10ra, 19ra, 22vb), his brother ʿƎquba Libanos (e.g., fols. 12rb, 14va, 19ra, 22vb) and his children Wäldä Yoḥannǝs (e.g., fols. 11ra, 16rb, 21va), Wäldä Maryam (e.g., fols. 11ra, 16rb, 21va), Gäbrä Ḥǝywät Solomon (e.g., fols. 15va, 21va), Wälättä Ḥǝywät (e.g., fols. 15va, 25ra), and Gäbrä Giyorgis (e.g., fols. 9vb, 10ra). &#xD;
Also, they are mentioned on fol. 48rb (s. Additio 1). &#xD;
&#xD;
Mss. MR-001 and MR-009 (both written by Wäldä Muse) were commissioned by the same donors. SMM-006 was also donated by the same family (the name of the scribe is also the same, Wäldä Muse, but the handwriting appears different).</persName>
